Articles.Content: I launched, orbited kerbin. I did a little bit of science. I recovered the craft and when I came back none of the science I did got saved. I should have gained about 45 science and non of it. The science tab in the recovery was greyed out. I am not sure what's going on.
The mono.dll is usually your computer trying to pass the 3.5GB ram limit in 32bit unity. I'm fairly sure the mods that add more planets are mostly not compatible with each other.

Error occurred at 2015-01-01_201608.

F:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program\KSP.exe, run by Owner.

32% memory in use.

0 MB physical memory [0 MB free].

0 MB paging file [0 MB free].

0 MB user address space [122 MB free].

Write to location 00417000 caused an access violation.

Looks like you're running out of addressable RAM, I don't think we can figure this one out just from the error log, we'll need the output_log.txt and dxdiag as well, see the support stickies.

Also, fixed the scrolling
